HEADWORD: Dwarfish
<hw>Dwarf"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Like a dwarf; below the common
stature or size; very small; petty; <as>as, a <ex>dwarfish</ex> animal,
shrub</as>.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Dwarf"ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos>
-- <wf>Dwarf"ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dwarfling</ent>⟦br⟧
